WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.290
Dre:
I'm a drop-off dad.

00:03.290 --> 00:04.170
It's a time
to really connect

00:04.170 --> 00:05.580
with Jack and Diane.

00:05.580 --> 00:07.330
And I'm in good company.

00:07.330 --> 00:09.380
Jay-Z is a drop-off dad,

00:09.380 --> 00:11.710
John Legend is a drop-off dad,

00:11.710 --> 00:14.380
Terry Crews is a drop-off dad.

00:14.380 --> 00:16.330
But he probably
works out first.

00:16.330 --> 00:18.170
And I whipped her
right in,

00:18.170 --> 00:21.040
and all of the spots
in the parking lot

00:21.040 --> 00:22.500
said "compact"!

00:22.500 --> 00:23.750
Wait, again?
Yes!

00:23.750 --> 00:25.040
So, the city didn't listen
to your e-mails?

00:25.040 --> 00:26.290
Right?

00:26.290 --> 00:27.790
Well, I mean, this car's
not gonna fit in there.

00:27.790 --> 00:28.920
What did you do?

00:28.920 --> 00:30.620
I do what I always do.
Mm.

00:30.620 --> 00:31.880
I took two spots.

00:31.880 --> 00:34.210
N-Now, the key is to
make it look like

00:34.210 --> 00:35.960
you weren't trying
to take two spots.

00:35.960 --> 00:37.330
Mm-hmm.
You know, like there was

00:37.330 --> 00:39.380
a car that messed up
before you got there.

00:39.380 --> 00:41.710
Uh, you know what I'm
talking about, right, Diane?

00:41.710 --> 00:43.540
Mm-hmm.
See?

00:43.540 --> 00:44.790
Diane gets it.

00:44.790 --> 00:46.620
Well, I mean, you know,
ain't nobody compact

00:46.620 --> 00:48.040
going to Del Taco
at 10:00 a.m.

00:49.540 --> 00:50.790
Is that a shot?

00:50.790 --> 00:53.500
Huh?

00:53.500 --> 00:55.210
Get out of my car, Jack.

00:55.210 --> 00:56.920
Wait, what?
Get out of my car, Jack!

00:56.920 --> 00:58.210
Go to class!

00:58.210 --> 01:00.920
Hey, can you believe
this sucka, Diane?

01:00.920 --> 01:02.330
Eh --
[ Car door closes ]

01:02.330 --> 01:03.710
Diane.

01:03.710 --> 01:05.750
[ School bell rings ]
Diane.

01:05.750 --> 01:06.580
Are you
listening to me?

01:06.580 --> 01:08.960
What was that?

01:08.960 --> 01:11.250
[ Hip hop music playing ]

01:11.250 --> 01:13.000
How long have you
been wearing headphones?

01:13.000 --> 01:14.210
I don't know.

01:14.210 --> 01:15.880
When did you start
driving us to school?

01:15.880 --> 01:17.080
Hey --
[ Car door opens ]

01:17.080 --> 01:18.920
Okay, well,
you know what?

01:18.920 --> 01:20.620
We'll talk about this later,
baby girl.

01:20.620 --> 01:22.460
I love --
[ Car door closes ]

01:22.460 --> 01:23.750
...you.

01:23.750 --> 01:25.500
Damn.

01:25.500 --> 01:26.920
This drop-off dad
just got dropped.

01:26.920 --> 01:28.040
[ Car horn honks ]

01:28.040 --> 01:30.620
[ Honks horn ]
I got a horn, too!

01:33.420 --> 01:36.710
♪♪

01:36.710 --> 01:38.380
[ Groans ]

01:38.380 --> 01:39.540
Uh, what's wrong, Dre?

01:39.540 --> 01:40.960
Did you find out
that your sneakers

01:40.960 --> 01:42.500
are made by small children?
Is that it?

01:42.500 --> 01:44.000
God, it's so unfair.

01:44.000 --> 01:45.330
They can make
your high-tops,

01:45.330 --> 01:47.380
but they can't clean
the barnacles off my yacht.

01:47.380 --> 01:48.960
No.

01:48.960 --> 01:50.290
It's Diane.

01:50.290 --> 01:52.580
I believe it's pronounced
"demon," Dre.

01:52.580 --> 01:54.000
I --
[ Sighs ]

01:54.000 --> 01:57.080
I just found out she wears
noise-canceling headphones

01:57.080 --> 01:58.210
on our drive to school.

01:58.210 --> 01:59.380
That's not so bad.

01:59.380 --> 02:01.330
I'm the noise
she's trying to cancel.

02:01.330 --> 02:02.920
Ohhh.

02:02.920 --> 02:04.080
And I don't know
what's going on.

02:04.080 --> 02:06.710
Our morning drives
is our time to bond.

02:06.710 --> 02:08.210
I mean, we would roll down
the windows

02:08.210 --> 02:11.670
and take turns doing
Mariah Carey vocal runs.

02:11.670 --> 02:13.040
I don't understand it.

02:13.040 --> 02:15.330
The older she gets,
the harder it is
for us to connect.

02:15.330 --> 02:18.580
I, too, am more afraid
of Diane growing older.

02:18.580 --> 02:20.880
It's the older demons that
you have to watch out for.

02:20.880 --> 02:23.330
They -- They tend to
act the fool.

02:23.330 --> 02:25.120
Dre, it's okay.

02:25.120 --> 02:26.710
It's totally normal
for teenagers

02:26.710 --> 02:28.420
to not want to
talk to their parents.

02:28.420 --> 02:31.080
And for parents to not want
to talk to their kids

02:31.080 --> 02:33.790
and send you away
to boarding school.

02:33.790 --> 02:35.080
And boarding camp.

02:37.170 --> 02:38.670
Boarding Christmas.

02:38.670 --> 02:41.040
I never thought I'd say this
to a Caucasian,

02:41.040 --> 02:44.000
but, man,
I feel bad for you.

02:44.000 --> 02:48.170
The guys made me realize that
I had to do something quick,

02:48.170 --> 02:50.330
or Diane would be sending me
to boarding Christmas.

02:50.330 --> 02:52.040
To my son, David,

02:52.040 --> 02:54.330
following my footsteps into
the family business.

02:54.330 --> 02:55.710
Oh, to David!
Yes.

02:55.710 --> 02:56.880
Oh, my gosh.

02:56.880 --> 02:58.710
UCLA Medical School?

02:58.710 --> 03:00.830
Unbelievable.
How proud are you right now?

03:00.830 --> 03:02.620
The proudest.
Ohh.

03:02.620 --> 03:03.540
What about you, Bow?

03:03.540 --> 03:04.380
What's Junior up to?

03:04.380 --> 03:05.670
Junior is...

03:05.670 --> 03:07.120
Pbht!

03:07.120 --> 03:08.500
Um, he's killing it.

03:08.500 --> 03:09.880
Yeah?
Yeah, he took
a job in tech.

03:09.880 --> 03:11.120
Wow.
Mm-hmm.

03:11.120 --> 03:13.040
You know that, um --
the app ChoreBoar?

03:13.040 --> 03:14.460
Of course.
Oh, my God.

03:14.460 --> 03:15.790
I mean, I don't want to
toot his horn,

03:15.790 --> 03:17.830
but he's, like --
pshew -- fast track.

03:17.830 --> 03:20.000
Making that
Silicon Valley money.
[ Squeals ]

03:20.000 --> 03:21.170
Nice.

03:21.170 --> 03:23.380
I mean, he's
like a regular...

03:23.380 --> 03:24.920
black Bill Gates.

03:24.920 --> 03:26.170
That is huge.
It's so big.

03:26.170 --> 03:28.420
Delivery for
Dr. Feinberg?

03:30.540 --> 03:32.080
Oh, hey, Mom!

03:32.080 --> 03:33.500
Hey.

03:33.500 --> 03:34.620
Oh, boy.

03:34.620 --> 03:37.040
Bow, when you said
he worked at ChoreBoar,

03:37.040 --> 03:39.120
you made it sound like
he was the CEO.

03:39.120 --> 03:40.830
Mom, what did
you tell him?

03:40.830 --> 03:42.960
I was telling him --
Yeah, hold on.

03:42.960 --> 03:44.790
I got to
finish this delivery.
Okay.

03:44.790 --> 03:47.380
Thanks.

03:47.380 --> 03:48.580
Tch, tch, tch.

03:48.580 --> 03:49.830
You've been
ChoreBoar'd.

03:49.830 --> 03:51.380
[ Chuckles ]

03:51.380 --> 03:52.580
Are you
ashamed of me?

03:52.580 --> 03:54.380
Oh, of course not.

03:54.380 --> 03:56.620
I-I thought you were
gonna be supportive.

03:56.620 --> 03:58.620
I'm sorry, Junior.

03:58.620 --> 04:01.040
But in my defense, I didn't
expect you to be here.

04:01.040 --> 04:02.750
Well, I guess
maybe I should just...

04:02.750 --> 04:05.040
stop taking deliveries
to the hospital,

04:05.040 --> 04:07.880
because my job
embarrasses you so much.
Okay.

04:07.880 --> 04:09.920
You feel flustered.
Even though
the gastric bypass patients

04:09.920 --> 04:11.580
are my best customers.

04:11.580 --> 04:13.500
Junior, come on.
It was a white lie.

04:13.500 --> 04:15.250
It's like...

04:15.250 --> 04:17.960
Mom, I'm working
to support myself...
Mm-hmm.

04:17.960 --> 04:19.380
...like you
wanted me to.
Yep.

04:19.380 --> 04:21.380
Now, if you'll
excuse me,

04:21.380 --> 04:23.750
got to go hang a TV
at a retirement home.

04:23.750 --> 04:25.170
[ Laughing ]
That's my kid.

04:25.170 --> 04:26.120
Ha!

04:26.120 --> 04:27.920
Piece of
my celebration cake?

04:27.920 --> 04:29.670
Choke on it,
Feinberg.

04:29.670 --> 04:31.620
♪♪

04:31.620 --> 04:35.380
So, I went home to fix
my relationship with Diane,

04:35.380 --> 04:37.960
one baked good at a time.
[ Sniffs ]

04:37.960 --> 04:40.000
Hey, Diane!

04:40.000 --> 04:42.540
For no reason, I bought you
a cranberry scone.

04:42.540 --> 04:45.250
Mm, not really
a dinner-scone person.

04:45.250 --> 04:46.790
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
Oh, I got to
take this.

04:46.790 --> 04:48.710
[ Clears throat ]

04:48.710 --> 04:50.250
[ Groans angrily ]

04:54.250 --> 04:56.830
Hey, whoa!

04:56.830 --> 04:58.290
Was that scone
still good?

04:58.290 --> 04:59.670
Not good enough
to save

04:59.670 --> 05:01.460
my relationship
with my daughter.
Uh-huh.

05:01.460 --> 05:03.210
I don't know how
I'm gonna bridge this gap.

05:03.210 --> 05:04.880
Alright, you don't understand
what will happen

05:04.880 --> 05:06.500
if Diane doesn't have
a strong relationship

05:06.500 --> 05:07.500
with her father.

05:07.500 --> 05:09.250
Girls with
daddy issues --

05:09.250 --> 05:10.250
they make terrible choices
in life.

05:10.250 --> 05:11.880
Bow, they --

05:11.880 --> 05:13.290
They date
horrible guys.

05:13.290 --> 05:15.330
They end up
being strippers!

05:15.330 --> 05:16.420
Uh --
[ Muffled scream ]

05:16.420 --> 05:20.000
Diane is not gonna
become a stripper.

05:20.000 --> 05:21.540
Strippers can wear
glasses, too, Bow.

05:21.540 --> 05:22.580
I've seen it.

05:22.580 --> 05:24.120
Okay.
I've seen it!

05:24.120 --> 05:27.500
I've known a lot of girls
with daddy issues, alright?

05:27.500 --> 05:28.920
A lot.
Alright?

05:28.920 --> 05:31.170
There was, uh,
Watana, Ruthie,

05:31.170 --> 05:33.620
Demi, Dawn,
LaShawn...

05:33.620 --> 05:35.080
There was her sister --

05:35.080 --> 05:36.210
I can't even
remember her name.
What?

05:36.210 --> 05:38.750
I don't know who
those poor ladies are,

05:38.750 --> 05:42.080
but you are blowing this
out of proportion.

05:42.080 --> 05:44.920
I don't even know how
to hold a conversation
with Diane anymore.

05:44.920 --> 05:47.250
It's like I'm a stagehand
trying to talk to Rihanna.

05:47.250 --> 05:49.290
You can't
take it personally.

05:49.290 --> 05:51.960
Right now,
there are two Dianes.

05:51.960 --> 05:53.620
Sometimes,
she's my best friend,

05:53.620 --> 05:55.040
and other times,

05:55.040 --> 05:57.330
I do not want to walk
down the stairs in front of her.

05:57.330 --> 05:59.880
But I want
the best friend Diane right now.

05:59.880 --> 06:01.080
Well, you can't just
get it, Dre.

06:01.080 --> 06:03.000
She's a 13-year-old girl.

06:03.000 --> 06:05.000
She shows up
when she shows up.

06:05.000 --> 06:06.250
And what
you need to know

06:06.250 --> 06:10.290
is that you are
not in control.

06:10.290 --> 06:14.960
You just got to...
wait for the right wave.

06:14.960 --> 06:17.420
Well, when is
that right wave, Bow?

06:17.420 --> 06:18.210
Huh?

06:18.210 --> 06:20.330
Don't do anything, Dre.

06:20.330 --> 06:21.670
Don't force it.

06:21.670 --> 06:23.040
I can do that.

06:23.040 --> 06:25.120
Be patient.
Okay.

06:25.120 --> 06:28.830
Okay, totally,
totally.
What?

06:28.830 --> 06:30.420
Totally.
Dr-- Dre?

06:30.420 --> 06:31.380
Dre!

06:31.380 --> 06:32.750
[ Chuckles ]
I know.

06:32.750 --> 06:34.500
You can talk
in the morning.

06:34.500 --> 06:36.380
We're bonding.

06:36.380 --> 06:38.420
♪♪

06:41.880 --> 06:43.710
Bow could wait for waves
if she wanted,

06:43.710 --> 06:45.210
but I'm a man of action.

06:45.210 --> 06:49.670
Call me Daddy Du-rag,
because I'm making waves.

06:49.670 --> 06:53.170
What if I told you
there was a film

06:53.170 --> 06:55.620
where a man was
screaming for no reason

06:55.620 --> 06:58.210
and carrying a baseball bat
in school?

06:58.210 --> 07:01.790
That movie
is "Lean on Me."

07:01.790 --> 07:04.790
It stars a young old
Morgan Freeman

07:04.790 --> 07:07.040
who uses a megaphone
as a weapon.

07:07.040 --> 07:09.120
Oh, you're gonna
love it.

07:09.120 --> 07:10.420
Alright, buckle up,
[ Ding! ]

07:10.420 --> 07:13.040
because this is his first day
at a new school,

07:13.040 --> 07:14.750
[ Ding! ]
and he's gonna
come across some kids

07:14.750 --> 07:17.460
who need
somebody to lean on.

07:17.460 --> 07:18.790
[ Laughs ]

07:18.790 --> 07:20.580
Why didn't you tell me
this was a period film?

07:20.580 --> 07:22.120
Because it's not.

07:22.120 --> 07:26.580
It was made in 1989
about 1989,

07:26.580 --> 07:28.120
so it was new
when it came out.

07:28.120 --> 07:30.460
So was the Bible.
Hey --
[ Sighs ]

07:30.460 --> 07:32.080
[ Ding! ]
Do you see the way

07:32.080 --> 07:34.080
that Joe Clark
is breaking the rules

07:34.080 --> 07:36.120
because he believes
in those kids?

07:36.120 --> 07:37.620
I've never seen
anything like it.

07:37.620 --> 07:39.920
You know you can't actually
chain kids inside a school,

07:39.920 --> 07:41.170
because then
it's a jail, right?

07:41.170 --> 07:42.620
No, he --

07:42.620 --> 07:45.290
he's protecting the kids
from the outside world.

07:45.290 --> 07:46.420
Can't you see that?

07:46.420 --> 07:48.210
Without their
parents' consent?

07:48.210 --> 07:49.500
I'm just saying,

07:49.500 --> 07:51.290
if Ms. Biggs tried to chain me
inside a school,

07:51.290 --> 07:52.500
she'd need
a bigger chain.

07:52.500 --> 07:54.000
[ Groans ]

07:54.000 --> 07:55.830
And I thought Coolio
was in this movie.

07:55.830 --> 07:57.040
I --
[ Sighs ]

07:57.040 --> 07:59.080
Ohh...
[ Ding! ]

07:59.080 --> 08:00.460
[ Voice breaking ]
That Morgan Freeman knows

08:00.460 --> 08:02.670
how to whip youths
into shape.

08:02.670 --> 08:04.750
And did you see how
they took the school's song

08:04.750 --> 08:06.040
and brought it
up to date?

08:06.040 --> 08:08.580
It's like I'm sharing a piece of
my childhood with you.

08:08.580 --> 08:10.540
How many times
have you watched this?

08:10.540 --> 08:12.040
Like 20.

08:12.040 --> 08:13.710
And I know
I talked a lot during it,

08:13.710 --> 08:15.620
so, you know, we can watch it
again if you want.

08:15.620 --> 08:16.830
No, I'm good.

08:16.830 --> 08:18.920
But -- Okay,
you want to --

08:18.920 --> 08:20.330
want to do
something else?

08:20.330 --> 08:21.710
Let me miss you, Dad.

08:21.710 --> 08:24.670
♪♪

08:24.670 --> 08:28.620
My attempt to connect with
my child was a failure.

08:28.620 --> 08:31.710
I had let myself
and Principal Joe Clark down.

08:34.040 --> 08:35.330
Hey, honey.

08:35.330 --> 08:36.330
Hey.

08:36.330 --> 08:41.040
I made you
some ChoreBoar snacks.

08:41.040 --> 08:42.460
Thank you.
You're welcome.

08:42.460 --> 08:46.460
Sorry I'm not taking these
to my job at Google, Mother.

08:46.460 --> 08:49.170
Okay. Okay. Come on,
come on, come on, come on!

08:49.170 --> 08:50.420
Give me a break.

08:50.420 --> 08:52.580
I'm sorry.

08:52.580 --> 08:55.120
But -- Just, doctors
are really competitive.

08:55.120 --> 08:57.580
And what was I supposed to do?
Brag about Zoey's Instagram?

08:57.580 --> 08:59.000
I mean...

08:59.000 --> 09:00.420
I needed a win.

09:00.420 --> 09:02.580
Yeah, I get it.
Thank you.

09:02.580 --> 09:05.330
And you know, I'm sorry I ripped
your head off right now.

09:05.330 --> 09:07.210
Don't worry about it.
I've just been
a little stressed.

09:07.210 --> 09:08.460
I'm sorry.

09:08.460 --> 09:10.380
I got a call about coming in
for a job interview

09:10.380 --> 09:12.750
for a full-time
position, but...
Oh!

09:12.750 --> 09:16.000
...I already committed to a
bunch of ChoreBoar tasks today.

09:16.000 --> 09:17.120
Oh.
So...

09:17.120 --> 09:18.880
Oh, oh, oh!
Wait a minute.

09:20.380 --> 09:24.500
I could do your ChoreBoar tasks
for you today.

09:24.500 --> 09:25.580
Are you serious?

09:25.580 --> 09:28.170
Junior,
I believe in you,

09:28.170 --> 09:29.750
and I want you to know
that I have your back.

09:29.750 --> 09:31.420
Okay, great.

09:31.420 --> 09:34.040
Well, you are going to be
taking a dog for a walk...
Okay.

09:34.040 --> 09:35.460
...giving a ride
to the airport,

09:35.460 --> 09:37.040
and doing an IKEA assembly.

09:37.040 --> 09:38.330
For the dog walk...
Mm-hmm.

09:38.330 --> 09:40.880
...you are gonna want to keep
an eye on Mr. Biggums.

09:40.880 --> 09:42.750
He is a lot smarter
than he looks.
Got it.

09:42.750 --> 09:43.920
And for
the IKEA assembly --

09:43.920 --> 09:45.250
[ Stammering ]

09:45.250 --> 09:46.540
Is it all
on the phone?

09:46.540 --> 09:48.670
I'm a doctor, Junior.
I got this.

09:48.670 --> 09:49.830
I can use a phone.

09:49.830 --> 09:51.380
Yeah, my bad.
Uh, here you go.

09:51.380 --> 09:52.920
Oh, my God.
Okay.
Thank you.

09:52.920 --> 09:53.880
So, good luck.
Thank you.

09:53.880 --> 09:55.120
Go get 'em!

09:55.120 --> 09:56.580
That's my boy.

09:56.580 --> 09:57.880
Alright.

09:57.880 --> 10:00.960
ChoreBoar.
Chore -- Okay.

10:00.960 --> 10:03.540
Nope, that's --
Okay, that's the flashlight.

10:03.540 --> 10:05.620
Jack!

10:05.620 --> 10:08.040
Come and help your mom!

10:08.040 --> 10:09.750
The movie thing was a bust,

10:09.750 --> 10:12.250
but I wasn't gonna give up
trying to bond with Diane.

10:12.250 --> 10:13.460
[ Sighs ]

10:15.790 --> 10:17.170
Hey.

10:17.170 --> 10:18.250
You want to go to
the trampoline park

10:18.250 --> 10:19.460
and watch people
get hurt?

10:19.460 --> 10:20.830
No.

10:20.830 --> 10:22.920
I want to go to the mall
to return a shirt,

10:22.920 --> 10:24.580
but there's
a 30-day return policy,

10:24.580 --> 10:26.120
and today's day 31.

10:26.120 --> 10:28.170
So, I'm just
gonna take a nap.

10:31.620 --> 10:34.330
If I couldn't
do something with her,

10:34.330 --> 10:36.880
maybe I could
do something for her.

10:38.540 --> 10:40.420
Hey, I have
40 years' experience

10:40.420 --> 10:42.710
of watching my mother
yell at customer service reps

10:42.710 --> 10:43.790
at JCPenney's.

10:43.790 --> 10:45.620
Grab your shirt.
Get in the car.

10:45.620 --> 10:48.500
We're going
to the mall.

10:48.500 --> 10:51.330
While I was trying to solve
Diane's problem,

10:51.330 --> 10:53.000
Bow was doing
the same for Junior.

10:53.000 --> 10:54.960
So, Junior,

10:54.960 --> 10:56.250
you always bring
your son with you

10:56.250 --> 10:57.830
when you're
driving people around?

10:57.830 --> 11:00.830
Ah, yes,
actually, I do.
Jack: Mm-hmm.

11:00.830 --> 11:02.250
We're really close.

11:02.250 --> 11:03.920
I'm her little man.
[ Chuckles ]

11:03.920 --> 11:06.790
Oh, can we offer you
a loose mint or some tiny water?

11:06.790 --> 11:08.040
Uh, shouldn't you have
turned left back there?

11:08.040 --> 11:09.670
Oh, goodness.
Oh, yeah.

11:09.670 --> 11:11.120
You know what?
I'm so sorry.

11:11.120 --> 11:13.330
Sorry, I'm new to this whole
ChoreBoar thing.

11:13.330 --> 11:15.880
Uh...
I-I'm actually a doctor.

11:15.880 --> 11:17.460
[ Chuckling ]
Yeah, right.

11:17.460 --> 11:18.620
No.
[ Chuckles ]

11:18.620 --> 11:20.120
I know, it's crazy, right?

11:20.120 --> 11:22.460
But, um, yeah,
I'm an anesthesiologist.

11:22.460 --> 11:24.120
Mm.
Sure.

11:24.120 --> 11:25.460
[ Cellphone rings ]
Maybe in your country.

11:25.460 --> 11:26.750
My count--
Hello?

11:26.750 --> 11:28.040
I'm in the car.

11:28.040 --> 11:29.830
No, it's a chick.
[ Scoffs ]

11:29.830 --> 11:33.380
I don't know -- seven?

11:33.380 --> 11:34.710
A seven?

11:34.710 --> 11:36.540
Are you kidding me?

11:36.540 --> 11:38.170
Spit in his water.

11:38.170 --> 11:39.500
Do it.
[ Spits ]

11:39.500 --> 11:42.250
This is nice, huh?

11:42.250 --> 11:43.620
It actually is.

11:43.620 --> 11:45.040
Being out
of the car,

11:45.040 --> 11:46.790
getting
a little exercise,

11:46.790 --> 11:48.330
some fresh air.

11:48.330 --> 11:51.380
Well, you didn't have to carry
a baggy for two blocks.

11:51.380 --> 11:53.290
[ Dog whines ]
Ooh. Looks like
somebody's thirsty.

11:53.290 --> 11:54.670
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, I could use
a good bottle of water right --

11:54.670 --> 11:56.080
No, the dog, Jack.

11:56.080 --> 11:57.500
Here, hold this.
Let me give him some water.

11:57.500 --> 11:58.750
[ Cat yowls ]

11:58.750 --> 11:59.880
[ Gasps ] Oh! No!
Oh, God.
Wait, wait, no!

11:59.880 --> 12:01.250
Uh...
No, no, no, no!
No, no, no!

12:01.250 --> 12:02.250
Go get him!
Oh, God!
Oh, oh, oh. Uh...

12:02.250 --> 12:03.500
[ Dog barks ]
Oh, Mr. Biggums!

12:03.500 --> 12:04.330
Mr. Biggums!

12:04.330 --> 12:05.750
Mr. Biggums!

12:07.000 --> 12:08.000
Mm.

12:08.000 --> 12:10.380
Alright.
Let's just do this.

12:10.380 --> 12:11.580
[ Sighs ]

12:11.580 --> 12:12.380
[ Ding! ]

12:12.380 --> 12:13.540
Yeah, but, Mama,

12:13.540 --> 12:16.330
I-I think this is
supposed to be a bookcase.

12:16.330 --> 12:19.790
[ Ding! ]

12:19.790 --> 12:22.540
We have put together
your bookshelf.

12:22.540 --> 12:24.000
Mm. We did that.

12:24.000 --> 12:25.040
Oh, yeah.
Yep.

12:26.000 --> 12:27.040
Oh!

12:30.040 --> 12:31.920
Tch, tch, tch.

12:31.920 --> 12:33.710
You've been
ChoreBoar'd.

12:33.710 --> 12:34.960
[ Groans ]

12:34.960 --> 12:37.540
Good God,
that day was long.

12:37.540 --> 12:38.880
Oh, the longest.

12:38.880 --> 12:40.620
I need a soak.
[ Sighs ]

12:40.620 --> 12:43.880
Being a ChoreBoar
is hard.
Mm.

12:43.880 --> 12:46.750
Those people are rude,

12:46.750 --> 12:49.040
and the tasks aren't
as easy as they seem.
Mm-hmm.

12:49.040 --> 12:50.460
And I think
I hate dogs now.

12:50.460 --> 12:52.000
[ Scoffs ]

12:52.000 --> 12:53.580
I don't know
how Junior does it.

12:53.580 --> 12:56.170
Yeah.
His life is hard.
Mm.

12:56.170 --> 12:58.080
But not as hard
as Mr. Biggums' life

12:58.080 --> 12:59.580
is going to be
on the streets.

12:59.580 --> 13:01.040
Oh, God.

13:01.040 --> 13:03.250
I walked into that mall

13:03.250 --> 13:05.750
like a soldier
walking into battle.

13:05.750 --> 13:09.540
Operation "Return Your
Daughter's Shirt So She
Lets You Into Her Life"

13:09.540 --> 13:10.790
was a go.

13:10.790 --> 13:12.170
Okay, hold on.

13:12.170 --> 13:13.880
Wait right here.

13:13.880 --> 13:15.790
I got this.

13:15.790 --> 13:19.540
[ Music playing over stereo ]

13:19.540 --> 13:20.750
[ Clears throat loudly ]

13:20.750 --> 13:21.750
Can I help you, sir?

13:21.750 --> 13:24.710
Yes, I'd, uh...

13:24.710 --> 13:27.620
like to return this shirt
for my daughter!

13:28.790 --> 13:30.380
Oh.

13:30.380 --> 13:32.790
It's outside
the 30-day window.
Mm-hmm.

13:32.790 --> 13:35.250
I knew you'd say
something like that.

13:35.250 --> 13:36.540
[ Whispering ]
Please.

13:36.540 --> 13:38.210
Please, you got to
take this back, man.

13:38.210 --> 13:40.120
I-I don't know
what I'd do.

13:40.120 --> 13:41.540
My daughter's 13.
Right?

13:41.540 --> 13:43.120
She used to look at me
like a god.

13:43.120 --> 13:44.500
I feel like
I'm losing her,

13:44.500 --> 13:47.420
and now I'm just some dude
that can't get anything right.

13:47.420 --> 13:48.920
I'm begging you.

13:48.920 --> 13:50.920
If I don't get
this money back,

13:50.920 --> 13:52.670
I don't know.

13:52.670 --> 13:53.750
[ Inhales sharply ]

13:53.750 --> 13:55.380
I don't know.

14:00.120 --> 14:01.960
[ Whispering ]
I get it.
Oh.

14:01.960 --> 14:03.460
[ Normal voice ] I have
a teenage daughter, too, man.

14:03.460 --> 14:05.040
[ Gasps ]

14:05.040 --> 14:08.120
She's got me in her phone
as "Captain Dumbass."

14:08.120 --> 14:09.580
Thank you.

14:09.580 --> 14:11.710
I owe you big time.

14:11.710 --> 14:13.000
[ Normal voice ]
Now be quick about it, man!

14:13.000 --> 14:14.750
We ain't got all day!

14:14.750 --> 14:16.580
Heh.
Captain Dumbass.

14:19.170 --> 14:20.960
[ Whispering ] Again,
you are saving my life.

14:20.960 --> 14:22.790
God bless you.
Mm-hmm.

14:22.790 --> 14:25.210
[ Normal voice ]
Thank you! For nothing.

14:26.620 --> 14:28.210
Wow.

14:28.210 --> 14:30.380
That guy's probably gonna
cry himself to sleep tonight.

14:30.380 --> 14:31.580
Thanks, Dad.

14:31.580 --> 14:33.330
Yeah, he's lucky
I'm having a good day

14:33.330 --> 14:34.620
or else
I would've went in.
Mm-hmm.

14:34.620 --> 14:36.580
[ Gasps ]
Hey.

14:36.580 --> 14:38.460
Let's commemorate
this victory

14:38.460 --> 14:40.750
with a father-daughter
photo shoot.

14:40.750 --> 14:41.670
Come on.
Come on.

14:41.670 --> 14:42.670
Anybody in there?

14:42.670 --> 14:44.120
[ Knocks on wall ]

14:44.120 --> 14:45.330
[ Laughs ]
Let's go, baby girl!

14:45.330 --> 14:46.290
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

14:46.290 --> 14:47.920
Alright.
[ Sighs ]

14:47.920 --> 14:49.500
These pictures
are gonna be great.

14:49.500 --> 14:50.710
Mm-hmm.

14:50.710 --> 14:51.920
I can feel it.

14:53.540 --> 14:55.540
Hey, what's going on?

14:55.540 --> 14:58.080
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

15:00.500 --> 15:03.210
Sorry, I just
got a text.

15:03.210 --> 15:05.040
Come on, you've been
giving me nothing lately,

15:05.040 --> 15:06.920
and I've been trying
really hard.

15:06.920 --> 15:08.290
You know, I just want to
connect with you,

15:08.290 --> 15:10.670
but you just keep
pushing me away.

15:10.670 --> 15:12.540
You know what?

15:12.540 --> 15:15.120
Why don't you tell me one thing
you wish I knew about you?

15:15.120 --> 15:17.290
Or one thing you wish
I would stop doing

15:17.290 --> 15:18.500
that drives you crazy?

15:18.500 --> 15:19.830
[ Sighs ]

15:19.830 --> 15:23.330
Can I just...
text you the answer later?

15:23.330 --> 15:26.080
Like, not in public
with people watching

15:26.080 --> 15:27.670
in the cool mall?

15:27.670 --> 15:29.830
Well, it was official.

15:29.830 --> 15:31.540
I was out.

15:31.540 --> 15:34.920
Now I was just some chump
in the cool mall

15:34.920 --> 15:37.080
getting dumped
by a 13-year-old.

15:37.080 --> 15:39.620
I know how it feels,
brother.

15:39.620 --> 15:42.170
Bring it in.

15:42.170 --> 15:43.620
[ Sighs ]

15:46.120 --> 15:48.040
Thank you, brother.
Mm-hmm.

15:48.040 --> 15:49.040
Thank you.

15:52.000 --> 15:54.920
I waited for Diane's text
for hours.

15:54.920 --> 15:57.920
I was attached to my phone
like a teenager on Instagram,

15:57.920 --> 16:00.460
but the only "like"
I needed was Diane's.

16:00.460 --> 16:02.710
Oof.
I know that look.

16:02.710 --> 16:04.040
Postmates is late?

16:04.040 --> 16:05.670
Don't go too hard
on the driver.

16:05.670 --> 16:07.250
The gig economy
is tough.

16:07.250 --> 16:09.250
No, Diane was supposed
to send me a text,

16:09.250 --> 16:10.830
and it hasn't
come through.
Mm.

16:10.830 --> 16:12.880
You know, maybe one of
the satellites are down.

16:12.880 --> 16:14.620
Uh, send me
a test text.

16:14.620 --> 16:16.380
Oh, sure.

16:16.380 --> 16:17.880
Um...

16:17.880 --> 16:19.460
[ Cellphone keyboard clacking ]
[ Chuckles ]

16:19.460 --> 16:20.420
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Done.

16:20.420 --> 16:22.120
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

16:22.120 --> 16:23.920
Eh --

16:23.920 --> 16:25.500
"Thirsty much?"

16:25.500 --> 16:27.380
Nice, Jack.

16:27.380 --> 16:28.960
Alright, my relationship
with Diane is on the line

16:28.960 --> 16:30.330
and you got jokes?

16:30.330 --> 16:31.920
Yeah, well, maybe
her phone's broken.

16:31.920 --> 16:33.710
She's probably
just busy.

16:33.710 --> 16:34.710
[ Cellphone chimes ]

16:34.710 --> 16:36.080
Oh, that's her.

16:36.080 --> 16:38.290
She's bored,
and she wants to hang out.

16:38.290 --> 16:39.750
Ouch.

16:39.750 --> 16:41.880
So, she texts you
and not me.
Mm.

16:41.880 --> 16:43.750
Can't she see the effort
that I'm putting in?

16:43.750 --> 16:45.040
[ Cellphone thuds ]

16:45.040 --> 16:46.210
You know what?
I'm done with this.

16:46.210 --> 16:48.080
I'm tired of my heart
being stomped on.

16:48.080 --> 16:49.080
[ Scoffs ]
Your call, chief.

16:49.080 --> 16:50.290
Alright,
you just make sure

16:50.290 --> 16:52.540
you let me know when
she gets married, I guess.

16:52.540 --> 16:54.920
And ask her if she wants me
to walk her down the aisle.

16:54.920 --> 16:56.460
Oh, well,
I mean, I'm --

16:56.460 --> 16:58.500
Obviously, I'll be walking her
down the aisle.

16:58.500 --> 17:00.210
What?

17:00.210 --> 17:02.500
I'm sorry, is this all
new information to you?
Yes.

17:02.500 --> 17:03.960
Oh, I'll just let you
sit with it.

17:03.960 --> 17:06.000
Because it is
happening.

17:06.000 --> 17:10.460
♪♪

17:10.460 --> 17:11.710
Hey, sweetie.

17:11.710 --> 17:14.170
I finished
your ChoreBoaring.

17:14.170 --> 17:15.880
Oh.
Here you go.

17:15.880 --> 17:16.960
Thank you.

17:16.960 --> 17:18.620
And it wasn't easy.
Oh.

17:18.620 --> 17:21.420
And it wasn't fun.

17:21.420 --> 17:23.210
It was hard.

17:23.210 --> 17:25.290
And it was terrible.
Mm-hmm.

17:25.290 --> 17:26.790
And I've discovered that
the only thing I'm good at

17:26.790 --> 17:27.580
is putting people
to sleep.

17:27.580 --> 17:28.830
Aw.

17:28.830 --> 17:31.330
Hey, you also
wake them up.
Eh.

17:31.330 --> 17:32.750
It's the most
important part, right?

17:32.750 --> 17:34.210
Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

17:34.210 --> 17:36.080
By the way, I was wrong
to be embarrassed.

17:36.080 --> 17:38.880
After doing your job
for an entire day,

17:38.880 --> 17:42.170
I know that you work
10 times harder

17:42.170 --> 17:44.330
than any of
those doctors' children.

17:44.330 --> 17:45.540
Really?

17:45.540 --> 17:47.830
Yeah.
And hey.

17:47.830 --> 17:48.750
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:48.750 --> 17:50.250
Can I tell you
a secret?

17:50.250 --> 17:53.210
Getting into med school
is not that hard.
What?

17:53.210 --> 17:55.670
There are a ton
of doctors

17:55.670 --> 17:57.080
who are dumb.

17:57.080 --> 17:59.330
H-How many is a ton?

17:59.330 --> 18:00.830
That's not the point,
sweetheart.

18:00.830 --> 18:02.540
I am proud of you,

18:02.540 --> 18:05.080
and it doesn't matter
what you do for a living.

18:05.080 --> 18:08.080
Thanks, Mom.

18:08.080 --> 18:11.080
But, like --
like, surgeons?

18:11.080 --> 18:13.670
Are -- Are there
dumb surgeons?

18:13.670 --> 18:15.460
♪♪

18:15.460 --> 18:18.380
I decided to
write my daughter off.

18:18.380 --> 18:22.080
It felt harsh, but I had to
remember it was her fault.

18:22.080 --> 18:24.120
I wasn't gonna
beat myself up.

18:24.120 --> 18:26.250
Four out of five kids
ain't bad.

18:26.250 --> 18:28.460
Mm.
Morning, babe.
Oh, hi.
Morning.

18:28.460 --> 18:30.710
Diane.

18:30.710 --> 18:32.500
Good morning, Dad.

18:32.500 --> 18:33.620
Is it?

18:33.620 --> 18:35.250
[ Scoffs ]
Dad's being weird.
Yeah.

18:35.250 --> 18:36.330
I'm gonna
go upstairs.

18:36.330 --> 18:37.460
Alright.
Bye, sweetheart.

18:37.460 --> 18:38.420
Bye.
[ Sighs ]

18:38.420 --> 18:39.380
Mm-hmm.

18:42.790 --> 18:46.000
I just had the most amazing
conversation with Diane.

18:46.000 --> 18:47.000
Don't care.

18:47.000 --> 18:47.830
She's dead to me.

18:47.830 --> 18:50.250
Come on, Dre.

18:50.250 --> 18:52.000
Guess what
she told me?

18:52.000 --> 18:54.250
That she wanted to be raised in
a single-parent household?

18:54.250 --> 18:55.540
No, no, no,
no, no, no.

18:55.540 --> 18:57.500
And then he chained the kids
inside the school,

18:57.500 --> 18:58.790
which I thought
was crazy,

18:58.790 --> 19:00.540
but Dad explained he was
trying to protect them

19:00.540 --> 19:02.170
from the outside world.

19:02.170 --> 19:05.000
Joe Clark was tough,
but fair.
Oh, yeah.

19:05.000 --> 19:06.040
That's the kind of principal
I want to be

19:06.040 --> 19:07.330
when I grow up.
Aww.

19:07.330 --> 19:09.250
Except for
the fair part.

19:09.250 --> 19:11.620
The movie's
a hundred years old,

19:11.620 --> 19:13.120
but it's still
so fresh.
Not a hundred years old...

19:13.120 --> 19:14.620
Do you let people
boss you around

19:14.620 --> 19:16.080
when you know
you're doing the right thing?

19:16.080 --> 19:18.380
When do you stand up
for yourself?

19:18.380 --> 19:20.500
[ Exhales sharply ]
I get why it's Dad's favorite.

19:20.500 --> 19:22.460
You know, I think I'm gonna
start carrying a baseball bat

19:22.460 --> 19:23.710
around school.

19:23.710 --> 19:24.580
What?

19:24.580 --> 19:26.040
I broke through.

19:26.040 --> 19:27.040
[ Chuckles ]

19:27.040 --> 19:29.330
I caught the wave!
Yeah, you did!

19:29.330 --> 19:32.250
Now you got to ride it
as long as you can, Dre.

19:32.250 --> 19:33.750
But you got to do
two things.
Hmm?

19:33.750 --> 19:35.500
Be patient.
Mm-hmm.

19:35.500 --> 19:37.080
And listen to me.

19:37.080 --> 19:38.080
Yeah...

19:38.080 --> 19:39.830
that's gonna be
impossible.

19:39.830 --> 19:41.750
You do remember the guy
you married, right?

19:41.750 --> 19:43.380
I know.

19:43.380 --> 19:45.080
But sometimes I hope.

19:45.080 --> 19:49.000
But for Diane,
I will do anything.
Mm-hmm.

19:50.210 --> 19:51.710
It's nice to know

19:51.710 --> 19:53.620
that my little girl
is listening to me.
Mm-hmm.

19:53.620 --> 19:57.250
Even if she keeps
her ear buds in.

19:57.250 --> 19:58.790
Yeah, you keep
this up Dre,

19:58.790 --> 20:00.960
and you might be able to
walk her down the aisle...

20:00.960 --> 20:02.960
with Jack.

20:02.960 --> 20:05.500
So, maybe our relationship

20:05.500 --> 20:08.040
wasn't going to be easy
for a while.

20:08.040 --> 20:09.580
But that's okay.

20:09.580 --> 20:11.750
I had a feeling

20:11.750 --> 20:15.000
we were going to figure it out.
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

20:15.000 --> 20:16.580
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Diane: Hey, Dad.

20:16.580 --> 20:17.960
There's nothing I'd change
about the way

20:17.960 --> 20:19.710
you embarrass me in public.

20:19.710 --> 20:21.250
I may not always
make it easy,

20:21.250 --> 20:22.790
but I'll always
be your daughter.

20:22.790 --> 20:24.710
[ Laughs ]

20:26.620 --> 20:27.500
[ Cellphone chimes ]

20:27.500 --> 20:28.710
Don't be weird about it.

20:30.540 --> 20:32.120
Okay!

20:32.120 --> 20:33.710
I won't!

20:33.710 --> 20:35.620
[ Chuckles ]

20:39.080 --> 20:40.830
Hey.
Morning, Doctor.

20:42.330 --> 20:43.250
Oh.

20:43.250 --> 20:44.330
Hey.

20:44.330 --> 20:46.120
Hi.

20:46.120 --> 20:47.790
How's your son feeling
about school?

20:47.790 --> 20:49.500
How's that going?

20:49.500 --> 20:51.380
It -- It was a -- There was
a little misunderstanding.

20:51.380 --> 20:53.170
Yeah -- Yeah, it turns out
that he was, uh,

20:53.170 --> 20:56.040
selling meds
to med students.

20:56.040 --> 20:58.080
It was at UCLA,
though.

20:58.080 --> 20:59.380
What I really
wish I had

20:59.380 --> 21:00.880
was someone to
pick him up from jail

21:00.880 --> 21:01.710
and take him to rehab.

21:01.710 --> 21:03.670
Oh! I have someone.

21:03.670 --> 21:04.960
[ Both laugh ]

21:04.960 --> 21:06.000
Tch, tch.

21:06.000 --> 21:06.920
Yeah.
Tch, tch, tch, tch.

21:06.920 --> 21:07.920
[ Both laugh ]
